Concord Street, west from Hudson Avenue, showing the north side of the street. Note the steeple of the 'First Presbyterian Church.

P. L. Sperr
September 6, 1939

"Hudson Avenue, north from Tillary Street, showing demolition where Fort Greene Houses will later be erected. The industrial plating plant is at the corner of Park Avenue. View 3 shows Hudson Avenue (left) buildings, between Concord and Nassau Streets. On the right is Concord Street and Public School No.14.

P. L. Sperr
August, 1939
Views 1-3
